{"abstract": "The evaluation of machine learning models using human-labeled validation data can be expensive and time-consuming. AI-labeled synthetic data can be used to decrease the number of human annotations required for this purpose in a process called autoevaluation. We suggest efficient and statistically principled algorithms for this purpose that improve sample efficiency while remaining unbiased. These algorithms increase the effective human-labeled sample size by up to 50% on experiments with GPT-4.", "referenced_work_ids": ["53f4fb0e9972989194368faf288ff8e3cba5bd60", "30c1f450040b65c23f758dbdee7f1daffe278eef", "0d6c4d483b36100b2dfa5a68411945d0d28eea39", "4df2b1e7d54fe5ad81dc2ed6774b93ef7891b3c8", "de6d82d1969742028374c18fcfe3b0e2c26adcc8", "a0a79dad89857a96f8f71b14238e5237cbfc4787", "96f75d06ce8bc26128f0af0071b374d065bf7d64", "3def68bd0f856886d34272840a7f81588f2bc082", "042fe4e996a1133e2c4c11f70aa2654e88f31687", "f6283c74a07122c04f3f20fbc1c84a7c41aa97b4", "0cfce36622a017a86c2248ebe5dfdd0f8d643df7", "d300a122fd79997c06c8a5f3b719d61e338e5ffb", "1cedc9f229368ef87c37b76ad5a686cd7c180610", "97a4d5afc484efe2c5c51dc44baedeaa441cf7a7", "3c8a456509e6c0805354bd40a35e3f2dbf8069b1", "948639e277867c41beecc89fa6c6c1b88e3e3fd6", "e0a7ab724afc4a598df7cfb39352b21f1b7f8c3e", "92f44bfc47dbe6b377bc5f4981697cb18c50efdf", "877c05a0248635b683f3506eca58ac9ef96b6aef", "d2c733e34d48784a37d717fe43d9e93277a8c53e", "686261e8a8c91c760a10747b49090ee55597aca6", "1a569c3349e6538947c4ddb0eed0307bfd5dad15", "d7da009f457917aa381619facfa5ffae9329a6e9", "1ed03e95cc2041a18b80415eea1b410af7f0f9c1", "88ae34fa89e35ebd15e4b8d44e288e757547a1ab", "3724784e99333503cd5ca9b44a7b4847d5f627fc", "7d47ee5f84103529f84297c98c21dadb4742e3ff", "cfad182f567b6a6d54a4dd517e0122692afca9fb", "4cd4ccd9225f0a3c79cd4c72bd171039e28f2ab6"]}